label: Hollow Body Hangs
description: Hollow body hangs help with back pain alleviation, spine decompression, and strengthening your grip. Switching from a dead hang to an active hang by activating your core muscles is key.

label: Frog Stand
description: The Frog stand is an essential hand balancing exercise, preparing you for handstands by developing balance and strength in an inverted position.

label: Hollow Body Holds
description: Hollow body holds are an anti-extension core exercise. They teach you about pelvic tilt and are fundamental for core strength.

label: Pseudo Planche Lean
description: The pseudo planche lean is a prerequisite for the full planche, focusing on the front delts and core strength.

label: Pseudo Planche Push-Up
description: Combining the pseudo planche lean with a push-up, this exercise is essential for building strength for advanced skills.

label: Tuck Front Lever
description: The tuck front lever requires significant straight arm and back strength, holding the body in a horizontal position with knees tucked.

label: Elbow Lever
description: The elbow lever is a cool skill that looks like you're floating, focusing on weight distribution and balance.

label: German Hang
description: The German hang increases shoulder mobility to superhuman limits. It is trained by gradually lowering into the position using a block or bench for support.

label: Butcher Block
description: The butcher block exercise is essential for achieving a perfect straight handstand, focusing on shoulder mobility and strength.

label: Pistol Squat
description: The pistol squat trains most of the leg muscles and requires exceptional hip and ankle mobility. It can be trained with progressions like step-ups and assisted squats.

label: Tuck Back Lever
description: The tuck back lever is similar to the front lever but performed past the bar, requiring significant back and shoulder strength.

label: Compact Leg Lifts
description: Compact leg lifts focus on core compression and hip mobility. They are essential for mastering more advanced skills.

label: Pike Push-Up
description: The pike push-up builds shoulder strength and overhead pushing strength, performed in a slightly inverted position.

label: L-Sit
description: The L-sit is a full body exercise focusing on core compression, performed by lifting the legs while maintaining straight arms.

label: Archer Push-Up
description: The archer push-up is a unilateral training exercise that targets imbalances and prepares for the one arm push-up.

label: Tuck Planche
description: The tuck planche is a progression towards the full planche, performed by holding the body parallel to the ground with the knees tucked to the chest.

label: Reverse Nordic
description: The reverse Nordic builds quad strength and stretches the quads while alleviating knee pain. It is performed by descending controlled without using momentum.

label: Straddle Sit
description: The straddle sit is an advanced variation of the L-sit, performed with the legs spread apart. It requires significant flexibility and core strength.

label: Shoulder Stand
description: The shoulder stand builds shoulder strength and end range strength for the handstand push-up, performed by balancing on the shoulders against a wall.

label: Muscle-Up
description: The muscle-up combines a pull-up and a dip, performed explosively to get over the bar. It requires strength and technique.

label: Handstand
description: The handstand requires strength, balance, and coordination. It is performed by balancing on the hands with the body in a vertical position.

label: Handstand Push-Up
description: The handstand push-up combines the shoulder stand and pike push-up, requiring strength, body control, and awareness. It is performed against a wall for support.
